content.description: Pro seems a little dicey but is actually good albeit a little sparse.   Expect to work for it.  Committing moves out right and a tenuous traverse under the bulge.
content.location: Start is same as Marsupium.  As you reach the crack in the small left facing corner put a long sling on some gear then work up and right to a small roof then into the shallow corner.  Work up hill then do a spooky down climb to the next level then it isn't to bad to get down the back side of the crag.

content.description: Fun moves to big ledge about 10 feet up just below a chossy roof and left facing corner.  Climb out right of the corner then back left to where you finally get good pro.  Another body length and it eases up and leads you into a big lower angle crack.  Thought this was a 9 Karl Rickson had done years ago.  Ought to learn how to read a guidebook.
content.location: Start is the same as Bownorthman but instead of moving right into the wide crack climb face right of short left facing corner.

content.description: Starts out with hard moves up a seam that leads up to a shallow left facing corner with a nice crack.  Rock is a little funky but can be avoided with some care.
content.location: Left edge of SE Face just before you would get to the narrow S end of the wall.  Starts in a seam with a nice little finger wedge.

content.description: Small Crag just uphill from Turret Rock.  Routes are all trad and on the SE face.  None are great but you can have a fun day there if you don't mind some spooky trad.  Needs some anchors at the top but you can downclimb off the top but it is spooky as well if you do the left side routes.
